NXGEN Technology AG
Local Mode
1. Overview and Purpose of Local Mode  
Local Mode allows the operator workstation to establish a direct, peer-to-peer connection (P2P streaming) to the
Network Video Recorder (NVR) or device, typically bypassing the central Genesis cloud streaming gateway for
these specific high-bandwidth functions.
1.1 Key Functionalities Enabled by Local Mode  
When fully supported by a device type, Local Mode enables the following features directly on the operator's
workstation:
Feature
Description
 
P2P
Streaming
Enables fast, direct video streaming access.
 
Live Video
Real-time video monitoring.
 
Playback
Review of archived footage.
 
Local SDK
Audio
Audio functionalities (including two-way audio and
audio announcements) directly through the local device
Software Development Kit (SDK).
 
Encrypted
Streams
Handling of encrypted communication streams from
the device.
 
Local PTZ
Pan-Tilt-Zoom control locally.
 
Local IO
Input/Output operations locally.
 
Timeline
Chronological navigation and viewing of events.
 
 
1.2 Device Types Where Local Mode is Not Applicable  
Local Mode operation is not supported or required for certain device types, as their integration is exclusively
cloud-based or their native functionality does not permit it:
Hanwha-Techwin NVRs: All features are explicitly noted as NOT supported in Local Mode.
Genesis Audio (SIP/Twilio): Not required; the device is designed for cloud integration.
InnoVi AI Cloud: Not applicable, as InnoVi is a cloud-based SaaS solution.
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000023910287/en
Senstar: Local Mode operations are not supported for Senstar devices.
Viasys Cloud NVRs: Do not support Local Mode operations.
2. Installation and Technical Prerequisites  
Local Mode components must be installed on every operator workstation intending to use the enhanced P2P and
SDK features.
2.2 Installation Steps (Customer & Internal)  
1. Download the Installer: https://sharebinary.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/Genesis-Installer-main-
v.2.8.2.msi%20a
2. Run as Administrator: The Genesis-Installer.exe must be run with Administrator privileges and follow on
screen instructions.
 
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000023910287/en
